Commentary: there it is! The pursuit of that last run has been like much of the rest of his innings. A bit of a struggle, some of his doing, but like the rest of his innings, he has survived, he has kept his head about it, and he's brought up the runs. Second Test hundred for Haris Sohail, got by tucking a full ball to mid-on's left. He's been good down the ground, and that's where he gets the big run. A relieved acknowledgement of the dressing room, most of which was in splits over the last few minutes. Kisses the ground, says a prayer, and a reserved smile from the man

The ball is pitched on middle and then straightens, but the only issue could be height, as it seems to have eluded both bat and glove, as Sarfraz looks to lap it down to fine leg. There's a hint of deviation when it comes close to the gloves, and that will be the decisive factor for TV umpire Ian Gould. Yes, it has taken the glove along the way, that too of the bottom hand!
